# Study Guide: Unit 06 - Direction Sense Test

---

## 🧭 Overview

- General Directions
- Casting of Shadows
- Distance Related Questions
- Left and Right Movements

These concepts are often tested in competitive exams like CAT and GMAT, where logical reasoning and visualization play a vital role.

---

## 🔍 Topic-Wise Breakdown

### ✅ 6.1 General Directions

#### 📍 Main Directions
There are **four primary directions**:  
| Direction | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| North     | Upward      |
| South     | Downward    |
| East      | Right       |
| West      | Left        |

#### 🌟 Additional Directions
Derived from the main directions, we have:
| Direction         | Between Which Directions |
|-------------------|--------------------------|
| Northeast (NE)    | North & East             |
| Northwest (NW)    | North & West             |
| Southeast (SE)    | South & East             |
| Southwest (SW)    | South & West             |

---

### 🌞 6.2 Casting of Shadows

Understanding the **position of the sun** helps determine the **direction of a shadow**.

| Time of Day      | Sun Position   | Shadow Direction |
|------------------|----------------|------------------|
| Sunrise          | East            | West              |
| Midday           | Directly Above | No Shadow        |
| Sunset           | West            | East              |

#### 📌 Important Rules
- Facing **Sunrise (East)** → Shadow is on **West**
- Facing **North** → Shadow on **Right (Sunrise)**, **Left (Sunset)**
- Facing **South** → Shadow on **Left (Sunrise)**, **Right (Sunset)**

---

### 📐 6.3 Distance Related Questions

To solve these types of problems, **Pythagoras’ Theorem** is essential:

$$
\text{If } \triangle ABC \text{ is right-angled at } B,
$$
$$
AB^2 + BC^2 = AC^2
$$

This theorem is used to find the **shortest path**, **minimum distance**, or **diagonal distances**.

---

### ⚙️ 6.4 Left Right Movement

When a person changes direction, their orientation affects their new direction:

| Facing | Left Turn | Right Turn |
|--------|-----------|------------|
| North  | West      | East       |
| East   | North     | South      |
| South  | East      | West       |
| West   | South     | North      |

---

